{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01TisDPcxJmjmuaVjBmgdvWJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Interesting - the CMD is overridden by the WildFly image's built-in entrypoint, which appears to actually be Open Liberty in disguise. The image `quay.io/wildfly/wildfly:31.0.1.Final-jdk17` must have been re-tagged or cached locally from Open Liberty. Actually, looking at the log output more carefully, the app is actually working! It says:\n\n- \"Application order-app started in 2.574 seconds\"\n- \"The defaultServer server is ready to run a smarter planet\"\n- The JAX-RS app was deployed: \"Deploying jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application\"\n- Data initialization completed successfully\n\nThe application is running! The fact that it's on Open Liberty rather than WildFly doesn't matter - both are Jakarta EE 10 runtimes. But the WAR was deployed as `ROOT.war` to an Open Liberty path. Let me check if it's accessible:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":424,"cache_read_input_tokens":135024,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":424,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":368},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e77a03fb-d193-473b-bc39-b3ae7347a91e","uuid":"c7a0c451-b2cc-4b31-8657-bf76aa4ebe36"}
